
[1]perpetuity

   PERPETU'ITY, n. [L.perpetuitas.] Endless duration; continuance to
   eternity.

   1. Continued uninterrupted existence, or duration for an indefinite
   period of time; as the perpetuity of laws and institutions; the
   perpetuity of fame.

   2. Something of which there will be no end.
